Comment: Jack Reacher is one of my favourite badass characters. The 1st Jack Reacher movie was absolutely amazing. It's to me a great mystery action thriller. Everything about the 1st Jack Reacher movie was dynamic, unique and different which worked great. Now the 2nd Jack Reacher movie is a step down from the 1st one. As a action movie it did okay for what it has got. Sadly the story isn't very compelling, or it wasn't told in a unique way. Cobie Smulders was actually the best part of the movie. She's strong, tough independent smart woman. The film has its plot holes, but it's entertaining. I'd rate it 6/10. Tom Cruise should deserve a 3rd JR movie, If so then I hope they capture the best ideas from the 1st JR movie. Just my opinion lol

Title: Jack Reacher: Never Go Back Official Trailer #1 (2016) - Tom Cruise, Cobie Smulders Movie HD
Comment:
Okay. I just finished reading the book. (This movie is based on a book)
Now let's see what scenes aren't in the book.

0:02 - 1:02 (They mention the phone call with Susan and Reacher many times, so it counts)
1:22 - 1:33
1:50 - 1:54
1:56 - 2:14

All of those scenes are NOT in the book.That's basically all of the action. And that's 1:35 of footage that's not in the book.

So basically the first movie got hate, because it didn't have enough action, so they just added a bunch of action scenes that weren't in the book. Don't get me wrong, this movie looks awesome in my opinion, but it's nothing like the book, unless in the actual movie it's like the book. But so far it looks like they added action everywhere.
And in this trailer they don't mention anything about Reacher having a daughter (that he doesn't even know of), or him being accused of a 16 years old crime, and those were the 2 main plot points in the book.

Title: Jack Reacher: Never Go Back Official Trailer #1 (2016) - Tom Cruise, Cobie Smulders Movie HD
Comment:
I write this as a fan of the action/thriller genre and anti-heroes in general (e.g., Mad Max, Snake Plissken, Jack Reacher, John Wick, any of Jason Statham's numerous gruff anti-hero characters). I enjoy Lee Child's books; I enjoyed the first Reacher movie, and, I'm looking forward to this sequel.

That said, it strikes me that if there is a flaw with the Reacher/Bond/Bourne movies, it's that the heroes have become, after so many iterations on screen, basically invincible. Reacher does get injured on (rare) occasion in the books, but, in this sequel, he looks pretty much unstoppable. Which invincibility is the guilty pleasure of this type of genre/material; I get it. It's undeniably fun to watch a hero kick butt and take names, like a force of nature. But, it does sort of remove any sense of real peril from the fisticuffs and gunplay. So, is there a way to pull off a balancing act of creating a hero who's tough, but, who is still not completely impervious to harm?
